      • RESIDUAL_OVERFLOW_FLAG_MASK

        public static final int RESIDUAL_OVERFLOW_FLAG_MASK
        Set for Residual Overflow. In this case, the Residual Count indicates the number of bytes that were not transferred because the initiator's Expected Data Transfer Length was not sufficient. For a bidirectional operation, the Residual Count contains the residual for the write operation.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • RESIDUAL_UNDERFLOW_FLAG_MASK

        public static final int RESIDUAL_UNDERFLOW_FLAG_MASK
        Set for Residual Underflow. In this case, the Residual Count indicates the number of bytes that were not transferred out of the number of bytes that were expected to be transferred. For a bidirectional operation, the Residual Count contains the residual for the write operation.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • READ_RESIDUAL_OVERFLOW_FLAG_MASK

        public static final int READ_RESIDUAL_OVERFLOW_FLAG_MASK
        Set for Bidirectional Read Residual Overflow. In this case, the Bidirectional Read Residual Count indicates the number of bytes that were not transferred to the initiator because the initiatorâ€™s Expected Bidirectional Read Data Transfer Length was not sufficient.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • READ_RESIDUAL_UNDERFLOW_FLAG_MASK

        public static final int READ_RESIDUAL_UNDERFLOW_FLAG_MASK
        Set for Bidirectional Read Residual Underflow. In this case, the Bidirectional Read Residual Count indicates the number of bytes that were not transferred to the initiator out of the number of bytes expected to be transferred.
